body:
# Write Documents

Write operations return structured acknowledgment data that tells you what actually changed. Agents should inspect those counts instead of assuming the write succeeded exactly as intended.

```javascript
const insertResult = await db.collection("users").insertOne({
  email: "new@example.com",
  role: "member",
  createdAt: new Date()
});

const updateResult = await db.collection("users").updateOne(
  { email: "new@example.com" },
  { $set: { role: "admin" }, $currentDate: { updatedAt: true } },
  { upsert: false }
);
```

Bulk writes are useful for migrations or repair jobs:

```javascript
await db.collection("users").bulkWrite([
  { updateOne: { filter: { email: "a@example.com" }, update: { $set: { active: true } } } },
  { deleteOne: { filter: { email: "stale@example.com" } } }
], { ordered: false });
```

Remember that `_id` must remain unique. Let the driver generate ObjectIds unless you have a strong reason to provide your own identifiers.
